<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17670429-65">
               <interp inst="t17670429-65" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670429-65" type="year" value="1767"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670429-65" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17670429"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17670429-65" type="date" value="17670429"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17670429-65-off362-c448" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-defend589 t17670429-65-off362 t17670429-65-verdict367"></join>
         
               <p>266. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17670429-65-defend589" type="defendantName">
                     James 
                     Clark 
                  <interp inst="t17670429-65-defend589" type="surname" value="Clark"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-defend589" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-defend589" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17670429-65-off362" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-off362" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-off362" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing 30 pounds weight of pork called bacon, value 15 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17670429-65-victim591" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Lacey 
                  <interp inst="t17670429-65-victim591" type="surname" value="Lacey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-victim591" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-victim591" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-off362 t17670429-65-victim591"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17670429-65-cd363" type="crimeDate">April 29</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-off362 t17670429-65-cd363"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670429-65-person592">
                  John 
                  Lacey 
               <interp inst="t17670429-65-person592" type="surname" value="Lacey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-person592" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-person592" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at the corner of <placeName id="t17670429-65-crimeloc364">Wych-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17670429-65-crimeloc364" type="placeName" value="Wych-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17670429-65-crimeloc364" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-off362 t17670429-65-crimeloc364"></join>, I am a <rs id="t17670429-65-viclabel365" type="occupation">cheesemonger and chandler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-victim591 t17670429-65-viclabel365"></join>; last Wednesday evening a piece of bacon of about 30 pounds weight, was taken from my shop door; I pursued the prisoner and he was taken with it under his arm, under the gateway in Lion's inn.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670429-65-person593">
                  John 
                  Crab 
               <interp inst="t17670429-65-person593" type="surname" value="Crab"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-person593" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-person593" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take the prosecutor's bacon; I acquainted him with he and I pursued, and we took him with it under Lion's-inn gateway.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I saw something lying in the gateway; I did not mind what it was, they said it was a piece of bacon, and they laid hold of me; I am a <rs id="t17670429-65-deflabel366" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-defend589 t17670429-65-deflabel366"></join> by trade.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17670429-65-verdict367" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-verdict367" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17670429-65-punish368" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670429-65-punish368" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670429-65-defend589 t17670429-65-punish368"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
